definitions.definition: A word (or compound term ) used as the title of a list entry or section, particularly in a dictionary , encyclopedia , or thesaurus .

examples: In "a very discerning car shopper", "shopper" is the headword .

main_definition: A word (or compound term ) used as the title of a list entry or section, particularly in a dictionary , encyclopedia , or thesaurus .
secondary_definitions: ( grammar ) The head of a phrase .
